'''Tuparetama''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 8.678 inhabitants and the total area is 185.54&nbsp;km².
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - [[São José do Egito]] ('''N'''); [[Iguaraci]] ('''S'''); [[Paraiba]] state ('''E'''); [[Ingazeira]] and [[Iguaraci]] ('''W'''). * Area - 185.54&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 560 m * Hidrography - [[Pajeú River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[semi arid]] - ([[Sertão]]) hot * Annual average temperature - 23.5 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 377.4&nbsp;km
==Economy==
The main economic activities in '''Tuparetama''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially creation of [[sheep]], [[cattle]], [[pigs]]s, [[goats]], [[chickens]]; and plantations of [[beans]] and [[maize|corn]].
